notes:
Returning to the scene of his maiden PGA TOUR victory, Rory McIlroy broke his own course record with a third-round 11-under 61 and shattered the 72-hole scoring record with his 21-under 267 winning total for a seven-stroke victory over Patrick Rodgers and Webb Simpson.   
   
 Earning his 11th career PGA TOUR title, Rory McIlroy surpassed Gary Player (10)as the international player with the most TOUR wins before his 30th birthday.   
   
   Rory McIlroy's seven-stroke margin of victory is the largest in tournament history. The previous largest margin was Anthony Kim's five-stroke win over Ben Curtis in 2008.   
   
   Rory McIlroy, who earned his first TOUR win at Quail Hollow in 2010, became the first multiple winner of the Wells Fargo Championship in its 13th year.   
   
 Playing on a sponsor exemption, 22-year-old Patrick Rodgers tied for second with Webb Simpson in his 16th start on the PGA TOUR and 13th as a professional.   
   
 With a T4 finish, Phil Mickelson extended his record for most top-10 finishes at the Wells Fargo Championship with eight in 12 appearances. He has now played 37 of 48 competitive rounds at Quail Hollow at par or better.   
   
   Justin Thomas and Sean O'Hair each made two eagles in the third round, becoming the 28th and 29th players to card two eagles in one round on the PGA TOUR in the 2014-15 season. Thomas eagled Nos. 5 and 7 while, O'Hair eagled Nos. 8 and 15.   
   
   J.B. Holmes missed the cut to become the fifth of the last six Wells Fargo Championship winners to miss the cut(36-hole or 54-hole)the following year( Sean O'Hair,  Rory McIlroy,  Lucas Glover,  Rickie Fowler -MDF, J.B. Holmes ).   Derek Ernst finished T30 in 2014 in his title defense.   
   
 Three players have completed in all 13 tournaments at Quail Hollow Club since the tournament's inception in 2003: J.J. Henry,  Charles Howell III and Rory Sabbatini.  
  
 Rory McIlroy became the fifth 54-hole leader of the Wells Fargo Championship to convert for victory: David Toms (2003), Jim Furyk (2006), Anthony Kim (2008), J.B. Holmes (2014).   
   
   Rory McIlroy played Quail Hollow's 16 par 5s during the week in 13-under par. Since 2010, no one is more under par on the 96 par fives. McIlroy posted three eagles, 52 birdies, 29 pars and only four bogeys(-54). His last bogey on a par 5 at Quail Hollow came at the fifth hole in round three of 2013. He has now played 39 consecutive par 5s in the event without a bogey.   
   
   Rory McIlroy broke the 54-hole scoring record at 18-under par 198. In 2011, Jonathan Byrd was at 15-under 201.
